In commit "validation: don't modify genesis during snapshot load" (86d48535198724c723370a447f73e134029331c2)

I still don't think it is good that if there are two blocks at the same height and one is assumed valid, then how the other one is treated depends on whether its _pointer address_ is higher or lower than the assumed valid block pointer address. (Previous comment about this was https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/23174#discussion_r732182831). I get that this only temporarily impacts validation state of the background chainstate, but I don't think validation behavior should be nondeterministic and treat blocks differently based on what addresses malloc returns. Would suggest just doing height comparison directly so order of vSortedByHeight entries with the same height won't matter:


```diff
diff --git a/src/validation.cpp b/src/validation.cpp
index 02b0f76f7b5..119b9141706 100644
--- a/src/validation.cpp
+++ b/src/validation.cpp
